          </div>
          <div class="leader-name">
            Anitta Krishan
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/anittakrishan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="leader-linkedin">
              <svg xmlns='https://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='18' height='18' fill='none' viewBox='0 0 24 24'><path fill='#444' d='M20.447 20.452h-3.554v-5.569c0-1.327-.025-3.037-1.849-3.037-1.851 0-2.134 1.445-2.134 2.939v5.667H9.356V9h3.414v1.561h.049c.476-.899 1.637-1.849 3.37-1.849 3.602 0 4.267 2.369 4.267 5.455v6.285zM5.337 7.433a2.062 2.062 0 1 1 0-4.124 2.062 2.062 0 0 1 0 4.124zM7.119 20.452H3.554V9h3.565v11.452zM22.225 0H1.771C.792 0 0 .771 0 1.723v20.549C0 23.229.792 24 1.771 24h20.451C23.2 24 24 23.229 24 22.271V1.723C24 .771 23.2 0 22.222 0z'/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="leader-bio" id="anitta-bio">After leading global people and culture strategy at TikTok, Grab and trivago, Anitta joined Hoogly to bring her expertise in HR tech and her passion for building human-centered, organisations. As Chief Culture Officer, she ensures Hoogly's values of trust and belonging are woven into everything they do. When she's not coaching clients, Anitta practices breathwork and travels the world to meditate in inspiring places.</div>
